HTML & CSS
Really fast at writing clean, efficient, and semantically correct HTML & CSS.
I always apply graceful degradation philosophy to my works, due to my extensive experience I almost
unconsciously apply styling patterns that result in posterior little or no crossbrowser debugging.
I have a good understanding of the pros and cons of SMACSS and use it in production environments.
I have experience with both SCSS and LESS and I'm pretty aware of the best practices to prevent them
from polluting compiled CSS.
Design
During my years as all round developer I was in charge of design as well and I learnt all the principles of
good design, composition and readability.
I'm really good at designing flows and thinking using time as the 4th dimension, being able to spot
problematic scenarios and design solutions for them in an interaction flow.

Source supporter I've been using most of the time the Gimp and Inkscape.
I'm extremely proficient with Inkscape and I use it as a tool to create wireframes, mockups, prototypes,
custom font sprites and SVGs to use in the web.
Usability and User Experience are extremely important having always the need to make something as easy

I've been always quite interested on art and design and I have been a drawing aficionado for more than 20
years.
